# /etc/ds-platform/api.env — TEMPLATE (DSO-100 spec §5.4; wave-1 increment #729 /
# DSO-134). Copy onto api-prod as /etc/ds-platform/api.env, root:root 0600, fill
# REAL values. NEVER commit real values. Consumed by the `api`, `portal`, `admin`,
# `centrifugo`, `sms-aero-adapter`, and `migrate` services
# (compose/api-prod/compose.yml) via env_file. Every NAME below is read by the
# built code — verified against apps/api/src/config/env.schema.ts,
# apps/api/src/main.ts, apps/portal/next.config.ts, apps/admin/next.config.ts,
# apps/api/src/room/chat.gateway.ts, and the sms-aero-adapter.
#
# The `ds` DB password here MUST equal POSTGRES_PASSWORD in data.env and the
# ZITADEL_DATABASE_*_PASSWORD in zitadel.env (one Postgres role, `ds`).
#
# QUOTING: besides compose env_file, this file is BASH-SOURCED by the deploy
# runbook (`set -a; . /etc/ds-platform/api.env; set +a` — infra/deploy/README.md),
# so any value containing spaces MUST be double-quoted (e.g.
# SMSAERO_SIGN="SMS Aero"). Unquoted, bash truncates the variable at the first
# space and tries to execute the remainder (`command not found`).

# === Core datastores → data-prod PRIVATE VPC IP (var.data_prod_private_ip) ===
# Host is the private IP ONLY (data-prod has no inbound public path — spec §5.1).
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://ds:<db-password>@192.168.0.10:5432/ds_prod
REDIS_URL=redis://192.168.0.10:6379
# NO PORT line here on purpose (DSO-100 on-box find): this env_file is SHARED by
# api + portal + sms-aero-adapter + migrate, and a PORT=3000 here overrides the
# portal image's ENV PORT=3001 → the portal binds 3000 and Caddy's portal:3001
# upstream breaks. The api defaults PORT to 3000 in code (env.schema.ts); the
# portal's 3001 is pinned via compose `environment:` (compose/api-prod/compose.yml).

# === Error monitoring (GlitchTip — DSO-125) ===
# Self-hosted GlitchTip on data-prod (152-ФЗ: Sentry SaaS rejected — ADR-0004 §15 /
# ADR-0005 §10). The api reports over the VPC to the GlitchTip web/ingest port on
# data-prod's PRIVATE IP (never a public host). DSN = the ds-platform-api project DSN
# from the GlitchTip UI, with its host rewritten to the VPC endpoint
# (192.168.0.10:8000). Absent ⇒ Sentry SDK is a no-op (env.schema.ts SENTRY_DSN
# optional); the api boots identically without it (like the IdP / Redis fakes).
# NO PII leaves the process (beforeSend strips request/user/server; breadcrumbs off).
SENTRY_DSN=http://<project-key>@192.168.0.10:8000/<project-id>
SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT=production

# === Identity provider (Zitadel) — issuer + OIDC app (spec §5.4, §6.1) ===
# The bare https origin Caddy fronts (must byte-match Zitadel's advertised issuer).
IDP_ISSUER=https://id.doctor.school
# The ds-bootstrap machine-user PAT captured at Zitadel first-init (README init
# step). Binds the REAL Zitadel adapter (with IDP_ISSUER); absent ⇒ in-memory fake.
IDP_SERVICE_TOKEN=<ds-bootstrap-pat>
# OIDC confidential-client creds emitted by idp/provision.sh (README init step).
IDP_CLIENT_ID=<from-provision.sh>
IDP_CLIENT_SECRET=<from-provision.sh>
# The Zitadel project that owns the doctor_guest role (provision.sh IDP_PROJECT_ID).
IDP_PROJECT_ID=<from-provision.sh>
# The api BFF OIDC callback — MUST byte-match a redirect URI provision.sh registers
# (run provision.sh with IDP_REDIRECT_URIS=https://api.doctor.school/auth/callback).
IDP_REDIRECT_URI=https://api.doctor.school/auth/callback
# Shared secret authenticating the Zitadel Action webhook (EARS-19 mirror sync).
# Fail-closed when unset (the webhook 401s); set it and configure the Action in
# Zitadel to converge the users mirror in real time (the periodic sweep backstops it).
IDP_WEBHOOK_SECRET=<random-hex>
# IDP_ORG_ID — optional; the adapter resolves it at runtime from the service
# account's own org and caches it. Pin only in a multi-org deployment.
# IDP_ORG_ID=

# === Audit ledger HMAC pepper (REQUIRED — #141 fail-closed at boot) ===
# Unset ⇒ the audit writer DI throws and `node dist/main.js` never finishes boot.
# Generate once, keep stable:  openssl rand -hex 32
AUDIT_IDENTIFIER_PEPPER=<openssl-rand-hex-32>

# === Delivery mode (spec §6.1/§6.2) — LIVE email + SMS for the slice DoD ===
# Unleash is out of slice (spec §8), so these env values ARE the delivery decision:
# `real` ⇒ the api's flag fallback treats email-delivery-real / sms-delivery-real as
# ON, and idp/provision.sh activates the matching Zitadel provider at boot.
EMAIL_DELIVERY_MODE=real
SMS_DELIVERY_MODE=real

# === Real SMTP relay — mail.ru business (spec §6.1) ===
# Consumed by the BFF MailerModule (real transport when email-delivery-real is ON)
# AND by idp/provision.sh for Zitadel's real SMTP provider (source api.env when you
# run provision.sh). HOST carries host:port; secure is derived from :465.
IDP_SMTP_REAL_HOST=smtp.mail.ru:465
IDP_SMTP_REAL_USER=noreply@doctor.school
IDP_SMTP_REAL_PASSWORD=<mailru-app-password>
IDP_SMTP_REAL_SENDER_ADDRESS=noreply@doctor.school
IDP_SMTP_REAL_SENDER_NAME=Doctor.School
# Portal origin the BFF duplicate-registration notice links point at.
MAILER_PORTAL_BASE_URL=https://app.doctor.school
# MAILER_SMTP_* is the Mailpit-intercept transport (flag OFF). Unused when
# email-delivery-real is ON (the real transport reuses IDP_SMTP_REAL_* above). Leave
# unset in prod so the intercept path degrades to a logged no-op.
# MAILER_SMTP_HOST=
# MAILER_SMTP_PORT=
# MAILER_SMTP_FROM=noreply@doctor.school

# === SMS-Aero (Gate API v2, spec §6.2) — consumed by sms-aero-adapter ===
# REAL SMS COSTS MONEY — the SmsBudgetService guards it; exercise with ONE
# supervised paid test. Prod creds otherwise live in Beget ~/.env; never commit.
SMSAERO_EMAIL=<smsaero-account-email>
SMSAERO_API_KEY=<smsaero-api-key>
# Sender signature carries a SPACE — KEEP the double quotes (header QUOTING
# note): the runbook bash-sources this file, and an unquoted space truncates
# the value and emits `command not found`.
SMSAERO_SIGN="SMS Aero"

# === Portal → same-origin BFF proxy (apps/portal/next.config.ts) ===
# Internal compose URL of the api; the portal rewrites /v1/* here server-side so the
# __Host- session cookie stays same-origin. NOT a public URL.
API_PROXY_TARGET=http://api:3000

# === Centrifugo — webinar room chat (wave-1, spec §5.4; #729) ===
# The api mints gate-scoped connection tokens and publishes over the server API;
# room chat is FAIL-CLOSED without the triple (no tokens minted, chat degrades) —
# all three are MANDATORY in prod. CENTRIFUGO_URL is the ONE origin the api
# derives BOTH endpoints from (apps/api/src/room/chat.gateway.ts): the browser
# wss URL (wss://<host>/connection/websocket) and the HTTP-API base (<url>/api).
# Caddy routes those two path families on api.doctor.school to the centrifugo
# container — so the value is the PUBLIC api origin, not an internal compose URL.
CENTRIFUGO_URL=https://api.doctor.school
# Generate each independently: openssl rand -hex 32
CENTRIFUGO_API_KEY=<openssl-rand-hex-32>
CENTRIFUGO_TOKEN_HMAC_SECRET=<openssl-rand-hex-32>
# Chat connection-token TTL (seconds). Optional — the api defaults to 3600.
# CHAT_TOKEN_TTL_SECONDS=3600
# Centrifugo-NATIVE duplicates of the two secrets above — the centrifugo
# container reads THIS file too (compose env_file) and env overrides its
# config.json, which carries no secrets. Each MUST byte-equal its api-named
# twin, or token verification / server publishes break:
#   CENTRIFUGO_HTTP_API_KEY                  == CENTRIFUGO_API_KEY
#   CENTRIFUGO_CLIENT_TOKEN_HMAC_SECRET_KEY  == CENTRIFUGO_TOKEN_HMAC_SECRET
CENTRIFUGO_HTTP_API_KEY=<same-as-CENTRIFUGO_API_KEY>
CENTRIFUGO_CLIENT_TOKEN_HMAC_SECRET_KEY=<same-as-CENTRIFUGO_TOKEN_HMAC_SECRET>

# === Object storage — Timeweb S3 `uploads` bucket (wave-1, spec §6.3; #729) ===
# Program-PDF uploads/downloads. ALL SIX keys are MANDATORY in prod: with
# S3_ENDPOINT unset the api silently FAIL-OPENS to an in-memory FakeObjectStorage
# (a silent prod failure mode — spec §10.8 asserts the real path explicitly).
# Values come from the Terraform uploads-bucket outputs (README wave-1 step):
#   S3_ENDPOINT      = https://<terraform output -raw uploads_s3_hostname>
#   S3_BUCKET_UPLOADS = <terraform output -raw uploads_bucket_full_name>
#   S3_ACCESS_KEY    = <terraform output -raw uploads_s3_access_key>
#   S3_SECRET_KEY    = <terraform output -raw uploads_s3_secret_key>
# These are the UPLOADS creds — never the pgbackrest repo keys (separate bucket,
# separate creds; backup creds stay in data.env — spec §6.3).
S3_ENDPOINT=https://<uploads_s3_hostname>
S3_REGION=ru-1
S3_BUCKET_UPLOADS=<uploads_bucket_full_name>
S3_ACCESS_KEY=<uploads_s3_access_key>
S3_SECRET_KEY=<uploads_s3_secret_key>
S3_FORCE_PATH_STYLE=true

# === Bot protection (Yandex SmartCaptcha) — ON for wave-1 (#186 rides #729) ===
# The SERVER half of the prod keypair lives here; the CLIENT half
# (NEXT_PUBLIC_SMARTCAPTCHA_SITE_KEY) is a portal BUILD arg baked at `next build`
# (compose reads it as SMARTCAPTCHA_SITE_KEY from the .env beside compose.yml —
# NOT from this file). Provision the keypair in the Yandex Cloud console with
# allowed domains app.doctor.school (README wave-1 step, owner-gated).
BOT_PROTECTION_ENABLED=true
SMARTCAPTCHA_SERVER_KEY=<smartcaptcha-server-key>
# Validation endpoint override — optional; the api defaults to the public
# Yandex endpoint (apps/api/src/bot-protection/smart-captcha.provider.ts).
# SMARTCAPTCHA_VALIDATE_URL=

# === Feature flags (Unleash) — OUT OF SLICE (spec §8); env fallback only ===
# Leave UNLEASH_URL/UNLEASH_API_TOKEN unset ⇒ every flag resolves to its env
# bootstrap default above (delivery = the *_DELIVERY_MODE values; bot-protection off).
# UNLEASH_URL=
# UNLEASH_API_TOKEN=
